00:34:21.645 --> 00:34:24.683
They told me that
all over the state
they had been seen.

458
00:34:24.717 --> 00:34:27.755
Some of those flying saucers.
whatever you call 'em.

459
00:34:27.789 --> 00:34:30.965
They gave me a book on it.
you know?

460
00:34:30.999 --> 00:34:33.140
They told me
to go ahead and read it.

461
00:34:33.174 --> 00:34:36.212
Well. it says
not to say nothing.

462
00:34:36.246 --> 00:34:39.456
Keep away from it.
Don't say too much. you know.

463
00:34:39.491 --> 00:34:43.840
NARRATOR: It was
the middle of the night
by the time Lonnie came home.

464
00:34:43.874 --> 00:34:46.705
MARY ZAMORA: I mean.
he was really pale.

465
00:34:46.739 --> 00:34:50.329
And I thought he was sick.
I said. "Are you sick
or something?"

466
00:34:50.364 --> 00:34:53.505
He said. "No.
I was just working."
He was like...

467
00:34:54.092 --> 00:34:55.990
Like he was angry.

468
00:34:57.716 --> 00:35:02.721
What I knew about it
was when I started
reading the papers. you know.

469
00:35:02.755 --> 00:35:07.105
Started coming out.
and everything.
I said. "What's this?"

470
00:35:07.139 --> 00:35:11.316
"I don't know." he said.
"It's just a headache "

471
00:35:11.350 --> 00:35:16.217
He said "Everybody's after me
and some believe me
