and eventually. a courier jet
came in from Washington.

1163
01:16:15.743 --> 01:16:18.263
He handed the footage over.
which was good. he viewed it--

1164
01:16:18.297 --> 01:16:19.954
-That's the last he saw of it.
-Exactly.

1165
01:16:19.989 --> 01:16:21.715
REPORTER: Did you know
where that footage went

1166
01:16:21.749 --> 01:16:24.372
of the flying saucer
that landed on the...

1167
01:16:24.407 --> 01:16:26.478
Went to Washington.
That's all that I know.

1168
01:16:26.512 --> 01:16:28.687
REPORTER: Did you ever keep
in touch with anybody about it
or discuss it?

1169
01:16:28.722 --> 01:16:31.828
How would I keep in touch
with anybody about it?

1170
01:16:31.863 --> 01:16:34.624
There's no way
within the military
or within the government

1171
01:16:34.659 --> 01:16:37.627
of keeping track of something
that is classified.

1172
01:16:37.662 --> 01:16:40.354
REPORTER: Did you try to go
after stuff like this?

1173
01:16:40.388 --> 01:16:42.598
We did. We have. It's there.

1174
01:16:42.632 --> 01:16:47.603
Are you saying that
there's some evidence that's...

1175
01:16:47.637 --> 01:16:49.984
REPORTER: Still hasn't seen
the light of day?

1176
01:16:51.192 --> 01:16:54.437
I'm saying most of it
hasn't seen the light of day.

1177
01:16:59.373 --> 01:17:01.444
MELLON:
Astronaut Cooper had spoken

1178
01:17:01.478 --> 01:17:03.791
with the President
at a Cabinet meeting.

1179
01:17:03.826 --> 01:17:06.138
He raised this
with Secretary Cohen.

1180
01:17:06.173 --> 01:17:09.452
And then Cohen's office
called me and asked me

1181
01:17:09.486 --> 01:17:12.489
to pursue this
and chase it down.

1182
01:17:15.941 --> 01:17:19.427
The Air Force colonel that I
spoke with got very frustrated.

1183
01:17:19.462 --> 01:17:22.327
and when I asked him
what happened to all
of these records. he said.

1184
01:17:22.361 --> 01:17:26.124
"Well. that was all cleaned up
or thrown out to save space."

1185
01:17:26.158 --> 01:17:27.263
something like that.

1186
01:17:27.297 --> 01:17:30.715
It sounded ludicrous.
but that's what he told me.

1187
01:17:32.855 --> 01:17:36.962
If there is some
recovered debris. say...

1188
01:17:37.963 --> 01:17:41.587
It is so deeply buried
and squirreled away

1189
01:17:41.622 --> 01:17:46.696
that it's outside of those
normal oversight processes.

1190
01:17:46.731 --> 01:17:50.079
and that's where
there's a problem in this area.

1191
01:17:56.741 --> 01:17:58.881
NARRATOR:
Dr. Jacques Vallee
has collected

1192
01:17:58.915 --> 01:18:02.125
purported metal debris
from UFO cases

1193
01:18:02.160 --> 01:18:05.335
dating as far back as 1947

1194
01:18:05.370 --> 01:18:09.719
that experts are analyzing in a state-of-the-art laboratory.

1195
01:18:09.754 --> 01:18:13.619
The breakthrough has come
with the invention of a machine

1196
01:18:13.654 --> 01:18:17.071
that enables usto look at the atomic structure.

1197
01:18:17.106 --> 01:18:18.452
and at that point.

1198
01:18:18.486 --> 01:18:21.731
the atomic structure
is impossible to fake.

1199
01:18:21.766 --> 01:18:25.804
This device is a multi-parameterion beam imager.

1200
01:18:25.839 --> 01:18:29.463
NARRATOR: Dr. Garry Nolan.
a Stanford microbiologist.

1201
01:18:29.497 --> 01:18:33.847
is using a revolutionary
three-dimensional
imaging device

1202
01:18:33.881 --> 01:18:39.542
to analyze the samples right down to their individual atoms.

1203
01:18:39.576 --> 01:18:42.096
When Dr. Nolan placed
some of the fragments

1204
01:18:42.131 --> 01:18:44.547
in the vacuum chamber
of his instrument.

1205
01:18:44.581 --> 01:18:47.584
he was astonished
to find their composition

1206
01:18:47.619 --> 01:18:49.759
was unlike any known metal.

1207
01:18:49.794 --> 01:18:54.833
Just one spot and the isotopic
composition all the way across.

1208
01:18:54.868 --> 01:18:56.697
NARRATOR: No matter
where he looked

1209
01:18:56.732 --> 01:18:58.872
in the sample's
jumble of elements.

1210
01:18:58.906 --> 01:19:02.703
whether magnesium. iron.
nickel or titanium.

1211
01:19:02.738 --> 01:19:06.776
the ratio of isotopes
didn't make any sense.

1212
01:19:06.811 --> 01:19:11.781
If you're talking about
an advanced material
from an advanced civilization.

1213
01:19:11.816 --> 01:19:13.058
you're talking about
something that...

1214
01:19:13.093 --> 01:19:15.440
I'll just call it
an ultra-material. right?

1215
01:19:15.474 --> 01:19:17.960
It's something
which has properties

1216
01:19:17.994 --> 01:19:21.273
where somebody
is putting it together.

1217
01:19:21.308 --> 01:19:22.999
again. at the atomic scale.

1218
01:19:23.034 --> 01:19:28.936
So we're building our world
with 80 elements.

1219
01:19:28.971 --> 01:19:31.421
Somebody else is building
the world

1220
01:19:31.456 --> 01:19:34.908
with 253 different isotopes.

1221
01:19:36.944 --> 01:19:41.569
I intend to use the information
to try to build something.

1222
01:19:41.604 --> 01:19:43.537
Try to understand
a physical principle

1223
01:19:43.571 --> 01:19:45.159
that we don't know today.

1224
01:19:45.194 --> 01:19:49.060
This material was manufactured.
It's not natural.

1225
01:19:49.094 --> 01:19:53.616
It's not natural
to the materials
that we have around us

1226
01:19:53.650 --> 01:19:55.894
in the lab. or on the Earth.

1227
01:19:55.929 --> 01:19:58.932
It does not mean
that it was necessarily

1228
01:19:58.966 --> 01:20:01.797
made some place in outer space.

1229
01:20:01.831 --> 01:20:04.523
It just means that
it was manufactured

1230
01:20:04.558 --> 01:20:07.043
specially for
a particular purpose

1231
01:20:07.078 --> 01:20:10.322
that we don't understand.
and we want to understand it.

1232
01:20:17.951 --> 01:20:21.713
MELLON: There is an immense
array of unanswered questions.

1233
01:20:23.094 --> 01:20:27.270
When we observe
some of these craft doing.

1234
01:20:27.305 --> 01:20:29.479
think about the possibilities.

1235
01:20:29.514 --> 01:20:32.482
what we may
discover technologically.

1236
01:20:32.517 --> 01:20:34.519
how we might solve
the energy crisis.

1237
01:20:34.553 --> 01:20:36.970
how we might raise
our standards of living.

1238
01:20:38.834 --> 01:20:40.870
There is an urgent need.
in my view.

1239
01:20:40.905 --> 01:20:42.251
to get to the bottom of it.

1240
01:20:42.285 --> 01:20:44.736
We don't know
the origin of these vehicles

1241
01:20:44.770 --> 01:20:46.738
nor do we understand
the intent

1242
01:20:46.772 --> 01:20:49.361
of whoever
is controlling them.

1243
01:20:51.916 --> 01:20:55.643
NARRATOR: There are cases that
seem to go beyond encounters

1244
01:20:55.678 --> 01:20:57.818
with an advanced technology.

1245
01:20:57.853 --> 01:21:01.201
to contact with
an engaged intelligence.

1246
01:21:02.029 --> 01:21:05.861
Papua New Guinea. June. 1959

1247
01:21:05.895 --> 01:21:09.554
An Australian missionary
spots a large disc

1248
01:21:09.588 --> 01:21:12.764
hovering just 200 feet
off the ground

1249
01:21:12.798 --> 01:21:15.905
while standing
with 38 other people.

1250
01:21:15.940 --> 01:21:20.910
This solid-looking
object and...
Can you imagine?

1251
01:21:20.945 --> 01:21:23.809
What it's like
to look up in the sky

1252
01:21:23.844 --> 01:21:27.917
and see some figures
up there?

1253
01:21:27.952 --> 01:21:32.266
NARRATOR:
All were amazed to see
four small occupants

1254
01:21:32.301 --> 01:21:35.994
dressed in what looked
like black diving suits.

1255
01:21:36.029 --> 01:21:39.825
Figures walking about on top.

1256
01:21:39.860 --> 01:21:43.622
and not the slightest noise
whatsoever.

1257
01:21:43.657 --> 01:21:46.453
And so we waved.

1258
01:21:47.454 --> 01:21:48.834
Wouldn't it be wonderful

1259
01:21:48.869 --> 01:21:52.597
if we could get this object
down onto the playing field?

1260
01:21:52.631 --> 01:21:54.737
And as we waved.

1261
01:21:54.771 --> 01:21:57.222
wondering whether
we'd get some recognition

1262
01:21:57.257 --> 01:21:58.706
and whether. perhaps.

1263
01:21:58.741 --> 01:22:01.226
they would understand
what we wanted.

1264
01:22:01.261 --> 01:22:04.057
they waved back.

1265
01:22:04.091 --> 01:22:06.956
NARRATOR: The encounter
lasted several hours

1266
01:22:06.991 --> 01:22:10.235
before the object
abruptly departed.

1267
01:22:10.270 --> 01:22:13.929
There was this amazingly
incredible speed

1268
01:22:13.963 --> 01:22:19.210
that the hovercraft
disappeared to nothing

1269
01:22:19.244 --> 01:22:22.834
across the bay in a matter
of a second or so.

1270
01:22:26.976 --> 01:22:28.840
NARRATOR: In 1994.

1271
01:22:28.874 --> 01:22:31.981
three days of sightings
across Zimbabwe

1272
01:22:32.016 --> 01:22:34.121
culminated in what
some believe

1273
01:22:34.156 --> 01:22:36.848
is the most significant
close encounter

1274
01:22:36.882 --> 01:22:38.815
in modern history.

1275
01:22:39.816 --> 01:22:42.198
Hundreds of people today
phoned the ZBC

1276
01:22:42.233 --> 01:22:44.718
and BBC correspondent
in Harare

1277
01:22:44.752 --> 01:22:50.172
saying they sighted
an unidentified flying object
last night.

1278
01:22:50.206 --> 01:22:52.381
We have some
eyewitness reports.

1279
01:22:53.416 --> 01:22:55.142
MAN: It almost seemed to be
under the cloud.

1280
01:22:55.177 --> 01:22:57.248
As it came past.
I noticed there's no noise.

1281
01:22:57.282 --> 01:22:59.940
and that's when I thought.
"Well. there's something
very odd here."

1282
01:22:59.975 --> 01:23:02.356
It was quite amazing.
It was beautiful.

1283
01:23:02.391 --> 01:23:06.947
They are saying that Jesus
is passing through Africa.

1284
01:23:06.982 --> 01:23:08.845
That's what they are saying.

1285
01:23:19.856 --> 01:23:22.756
TIM LEACH: We interviewed
about 64 children

1286
01:23:22.790 --> 01:23:24.068
in front of the camera.

1287
01:23:24.102 --> 01:23:25.862
UFO story that happens...

1288
01:23:25.897 --> 01:23:28.900
Just say exactly
what you want to say. okay?

1289
01:23:28.934 --> 01:23:32.214
Well. I was running
and playing.

1290
01:23:32.248 --> 01:23:35.010
and then I saw this maroon colorin the sky.

1291
01:23:35.044 --> 01:23:36.252
Why don't we follow it?

1292
01:23:36.287 --> 01:23:39.600
We saw this. like.
a silver thing down there.

1293
01:23:39.635 --> 01:23:42.051
It was a silver oval thing

1294
01:23:42.086 --> 01:23:44.640
that flew past really slowly.

1295
01:23:44.674 --> 01:23:48.092
I saw the bigger one
and the spaceship.
like. four or five of them.

1296
01:23:48.126 --> 01:23:50.025
It was red.
green and yellow.

1297
01:23:50.059 --> 01:23:51.267
There was this big ship.

1298
01:23:51.302 --> 01:23:53.994
It had these lights.
these patterns. and it flew.

1299
01:23:54.029 --> 01:23:56.755
I thought.
"No. it's not a UFO."

1300
01:23:56.790 --> 01:23:58.550
And then I looked
carefully at it.

1301
01:23:58.585 --> 01:23:59.586
and I thought. "Maybe."

1302
01:24:05.109 --> 01:24:06.834
NARRATOR:
Dozens of children said that

1303
01:24:06.869 --> 01:24:09.216
one or more
of the disc-shaped objects

1304
01:24:09.251 --> 01:24:12.633
landed just beyond
the far edge
of their playground.

1305
01:24:15.671 --> 01:24:17.880
The next thing they knew.

1306
01:24:17.914 --> 01:24:20.641
something was standing
next to it.

1307
01:24:24.369 --> 01:24:28.097
You saw him standing
by the silver thing.

1308
01:24:28.132 --> 01:24:29.892
And he had big eyes.

1309
01:24:32.860 --> 01:24:36.657
He had a big head
and big black eyes.

1310
01:24:36.692 --> 01:24:38.866
and was dressed
in a black bodysuit.

1311
01:24:38.901 --> 01:24:40.661
They were wearing
pure black.

1312
01:24:40.696 --> 01:24:44.596
And I came down
and I saw the funny man
with his eyes here.

1313
01:24:44.631 --> 01:24:45.942
and I saw a spaceship.

1314
01:24:45.977 --> 01:24:48.462
and there were a few
little ones around it.

1315
01:24:54.572 --> 01:24:57.161
REPORTER:
How far away were you
when you saw him?

1316
01:24:57.195 --> 01:25:00.302
Not very far. Not very far.
About a meter away.

1317
01:25:00.336 --> 01:25:02.442
-A meter away? That close?
-Yes.

1318
01:25:05.445 --> 01:25:07.205
REPORTER:
And how big was the figure?

1319
01:25:07.240 --> 01:25:10.312
It was about
as big as a grade six.

1320
01:25:10.346 --> 01:25:11.934
Yeah. it's there!

1321
01:25:11.968 --> 01:25:15.593
I believe that the children
did see something.

1322
01:25:15.627 --> 01:25:20.253
I believe them
because normally
children don't lie.

1323
01:25:20.287 --> 01:25:22.772
I've always taught my children.
"Seeing is believing."

1324
01:25:22.807 --> 01:25:24.912
Unfortunately.
I didn't see. So...

1325
01:25:24.947 --> 01:25:26.397
[CHANTING IN LOCAL LANGUAGE]

1326
01:25:30.815 --> 01:25:32.092
NARRATOR:
This alleged encounter

1327
01:25:32.127 --> 01:25:34.543
caught the attention
of Pulitzer Prize-winning

1328
01:25:34.577 --> 01:25:37.994
Harvard psychiatrist.
Dr. John Mack.

1329
01:25:38.029 --> 01:25:39.720
It seemed that he was
looking at all of us.

1330
01:25:39.755 --> 01:25:42.930
What did it feel like
when he was looking at you?

1331
01:25:42.965 --> 01:25:44.449
It felt scared.

1332
01:25:44.484 --> 01:25:47.418
It felt scary?
What was scary about it?

1333
01:25:48.488 --> 01:25:50.421
Well. felt scared

1334
01:25:50.455 --> 01:25:54.597
because I've never seen
such a... person
like that before.

1335
01:25:54.632 --> 01:25:58.946
And I saw this... person.

1336
01:25:58.981 --> 01:26:01.708
And it had big eyes.

1337
01:26:01.742 --> 01:26:04.193
That's all I saw about it.
Big eyes.

1338
01:26:04.228 --> 01:26:07.472
-They had short legs
and quite a long top.
-Mmm-hmm.

1339
01:26:07.507 --> 01:26:09.198
With a big head

1340
01:26:09.233 --> 01:26:11.718
and eyes
that are bigger than ours.

1341
01:26:11.752 --> 01:26:14.583
How much bigger than ours?

1342
01:26:14.617 --> 01:26:15.860
Four or five times the size.

1343
01:26:15.894 --> 01:26:18.449
Four or five times
the size of ours?

1344
01:26:20.865 --> 01:26:22.211
And then I was looking
at him. right?

1345
01:26:22.246 --> 01:26:24.075
-Yes.
-Then he was looking
at me back.

1346
01:26:24.109 --> 01:26:25.904
How can I just keep on
looking at him?

1347
01:26:25.939 --> 01:26:28.148
So I had to stop
and I looked sideways.

1348
01:26:28.183 --> 01:26:30.288
But I was looking
straight into his eyes.

1349
01:26:30.323 --> 01:26:32.911
Well. he never said anything.

1350
01:26:32.946 --> 01:26:35.673
It's just the face
and the eyes.

1351
01:26:35.707 --> 01:26:39.297
Maybe they're trying
to communicate with us.

1352
01:26:39.332 --> 01:26:42.162
Show us something
which we don't know about.

1353
01:26:42.197 --> 01:26:44.682
I think they want... Um...

1354
01:26:46.684 --> 01:26:48.444
people to know that

1355
01:26:48.479 --> 01:26:51.999
we're actually making harm
on this world.

1356
01:26:52.034 --> 01:26:54.243
and we mustn't get
too technological.

1357
01:26:54.278 --> 01:26:56.521
We don't look
after the planet.

1358
01:26:56.556 --> 01:27:01.146
All the trees
will be cut down...

1359
01:27:01.181 --> 01:27:03.873
and there will be no air
and people will be dying.

1360
01:27:03.908 --> 01:27:07.774
Is this an idea
you have had before?

1361
01:27:07.808 --> 01:27:13.642
Or did this idea come to you
when you had this experience?

1362
01:27:15.506 --> 01:27:18.888
-When I had this experience.
-Mmm-hmm.

1363
01:27:18.923 --> 01:27:22.582
NARRATOR: For the first time
in nearly 20 years.
the Ariel schoolchildren

1364
01:27:22.616 --> 01:27:26.102
gathered from the four corners of the world

1365
01:27:26.137 --> 01:27:27.518
to talk to each other

1366
01:27:27.552 --> 01:27:29.140
about the experience
they shared

1367
01:27:29.174 --> 01:27:30.797
that September morning.

1368
01:27:30.831 --> 01:27:32.350
I remember something there...

1369
01:27:32.385 --> 01:27:35.388
One they all still
struggle to understand.

1370
01:27:35.422 --> 01:27:37.286
You know that it's moving.
but you...

1371
01:27:37.321 --> 01:27:39.392
SALMA SIDDICK:
I stand by what I saw.

1372
01:27:39.426 --> 01:27:44.155
There was no reason
for any of us.

1373
01:27:44.189 --> 01:27:45.984
to make that up.

1374
01:27:46.019 --> 01:27:48.780
EMMA JELIC KRISTIANSEN:
I've not spoken
to anybody about it.

1375
01:27:48.815 --> 01:27:50.161
Not because
I'm not proud of it.

1376
01:27:50.195 --> 01:27:53.682
but because I don't
want the... The stigma.

1377
01:27:55.615 --> 01:27:57.306
LISIL FIELD:
So it's something that

1378
01:27:57.341 --> 01:28:01.828
I've had to deal with
for 19-and-a-half years.

1379
01:28:03.381 --> 01:28:04.969
I don't wanna say
I felt like I knew it.

1380
01:28:05.003 --> 01:28:07.454
-but I knew that I didn't
have to be afraid of it.
-Yeah.

1381
01:28:07.489 --> 01:28:10.146
NARRATOR: They took us back
to the moment of contact.

1382
01:28:10.181 --> 01:28:12.217
Exactly how I felt.
Exactly...

1383
01:28:12.252 --> 01:28:15.428
The details
still seared into memory.

1384
01:28:15.462 --> 01:28:19.017
I was with one of the other
girls and saying to her.

1385
01:28:19.052 --> 01:28:21.157
"This is amazing."

1386
01:28:21.192 --> 01:28:24.160
We all were just
stopped in our tracks.

1387
01:28:25.369 --> 01:28:28.682
A little man appeared.

1388
01:28:28.717 --> 01:28:30.477
On top of the actual craft.

1389
01:28:30.512 --> 01:28:33.342
And that moment. for me.
was very distinct.

1390
01:28:33.377 --> 01:28:35.379
because I was like.
"That's not human."

1391
01:28:35.413 --> 01:28:38.520
Well. I was just completely
engulfed in these eyes.

1392
01:28:38.554 --> 01:28:41.523
The eyes. and in that moment.
however long it was.

1393
01:28:41.557 --> 01:28:43.939
'cause I have no idea
of the time frame.

1394
01:28:43.973 --> 01:28:45.458
it was just mesmerizing.

1395
01:28:45.492 --> 01:28:50.773
There was no talking.
Um... It's all just images
in the head.

1396
01:28:53.328 --> 01:28:55.330
Telepathic communication.

1397
01:28:56.365 --> 01:28:58.367
SIDDICK: They were trying
to communicate.

1398
01:28:58.402 --> 01:29:00.369
Trying to tell us something.

